name: dl-n-acetylhomocysteine thiolactone
Reason: 1-ethylpiperazine-2,3-dione has a melting point of 116 degrees Celsius. The basic unit, piperazine, has a melting point of 106 degrees Celsius. The introduction of an ethyl group generally lowers the melting point due to the reduced molecular weight and van der Waals interactions. Each ethyl group can lower the melting point by approximately -10 degrees Celsius.
